-jmeter-testing-using-docker.html\">Distributed JMeter testing using Docker</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://medium.com/@ellenhuang523/a-docker-solution-to-jmeter-influxdb-grafana-performance-testing-568848de7a0f\">A Docker solution to JMeter + InfluxDB + Grafana performance testing</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/intuit/autometer\">AutoMeter</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/intuit/autometer\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">44</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":44,\"repo\":\"intuit/autometer\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - An automation tool for scaling load tests using distributed slaves, based on JMeter master-slave architecture.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2016-03-11T15:42:10.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"aliesbelik/awesome-jmeter","categoryHTML":"<h2>Distributed Testing</h2>","itemHTML":"<li>Testing in Cloud\n<ul>\n<li>Kubernetes\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/kubernauts/jmeter-kubernetes\">jmeter-kubernetes</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/kubernauts/jmeter-kubernetes\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px